SIMPLE: hurtful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hurtful
<hw>Hurt"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tending to impair or
damage; injurious; mischievous; occasioning loss or injury; <as>as,
<ex>hurtful</ex> words or conduct</as>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Pernicious; harmful; baneful; prejudicial;
detrimental; disadvantageous; mischievous; injurious; noxious;
unwholesome; destructive.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Hurt"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Hurt"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hurting</ent>⟦br⟧
